title: 71: Cicero's "On Doody" [sic], Book I
dc:creator: A.J. Hanenburg
description: Cicero was a legendary statesman and orator. He wrote a treatise on moral philosophy to his son in the hopes that his son would follow in his footsteps. In this episode, we review part one (with parts two and three to come), and make a few poop jokes. Heh. Doody.
itunes:author: Bees, Tweez, and Geez
itunes:subtitle: Ha. Doody.
